The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Saturday, December 27, 2003 				 Scuffle at Uttarayan entrance
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Santiniketan, Dec. 26: The security personnel of Visva-Bharati today allegedly abused and assaulted tourists who came to see Uttarayan, the two-storey house of Rabindranath Tagore that is now a museum. 																								Visva-Bharati sources said the building was closed to visitors today but the tourists insisted that they be allowed inside. A minor scuffle followed and the tourists claimed that four of them were injured.																								Vice-chancellor Sujit Basu expressed regret and said action will be taken against the security guards if they are found guilty. We are ashamed of what happened. But the security staff responsible will be punished, said Basu. He also went to see the injured at the Pearson Memorial Hospital but they had been released.
